        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Please mark as Draft until this is ready.\r\n\r\nThe code looks a bit more \"busy\" than I expected, is there a way to simplify it?\r\n\r\n> should I encourage users in the docs to use the new format when they use a callback (just add examples like this and remove old ones)?\r\n\r\nDon't need to \"encourage\", but I do think we should update all examples to use the function-last form.\r\n\r\nThere are a lot of downvotes on https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/28536 , but I assume they are addressed by https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/28536#issuecomment-2081528222 which has upvotes.",
