            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Well I personally also don't really like adding this\r\n\r\nwhy? It seems unintuitive that RHS (\"right hand side\") is not the right-most arg. `opts` are just parameters, why are they separated from the left most parameters? The main part of every mapping is its actual definition, placing that in the middle of the args seems completely random.\r\n\r\nAnd by making this an overload (which seems pretty natural and would be a common approach in any language that supports overloads), there is no cost.",
