        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> That is simply a limitation of the API, which does not support variable \"arity\" of function signatures\r\n\r\n> API is a low-level extension point for exposing internals. It's irrelevant for Lua which is a high-level interface intended to be maximally ergonomic.\r\n\r\nik but it's also used a lot in lua code and therefor people are used to having `opts` last\r\n\r\n>  LHS is visually what one looks for, so it's useful for it to be near the start.\r\n\r\nbut people also look for the rhs and it also should be there imo\r\nthat's what the rest of my comment was about",
