        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> ..., but I do think we should update all examples to use the function-last form.\r\n\r\n> the legacy signature\r\n\r\nThe current signature is better IMO, it shouldn't become legacy.\r\n\r\n> There are a lot of downvotes on https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/28536 , but I assume they are addressed by https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/28536#issuecomment-2081528222 which has upvotes.\r\n\r\nI think people are ok with adding an _alternative_ where opts are in the middle, and that is the overload (as #28536 specifies).\r\n\r\nI think people dislike this change because it really doesn't solve any problems. The motivation seems to be to just unnecessarily apply the _guildeline_ (not rule) of function as the last argument. And note `rhs` is often not a function. As an example, in my [config](https://github.com/lewis6991/dotfiles/blob/91402eeb8b870f72f22468d4c23654c175b048c7/config/nvim/lua/lewis6991/init.lua#L143-L252), about 50% of my mappings use a string, 50% use opts, and less than 10% use an anonymous function, so this new signature wouldn't improve anything.",
